───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
MODIFICATIONS FROM ORIGINAL
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The following modifications were made to Nick Mark's original physics engine:

1. Elastance shape factor: n changed from 8 to 3 (smoother activation curve,
   prevents unrealistic LVP spikes above aortic pressure in normal physiology)

2. Aortic valve conductance: kAv increased from 18 to 28 mL/s/mmHg
   (faster valve opening; LVP-AoP gradient equalises physiologically)

3. Windkessel runoff resistance: Rr reduced from 1.2 to 0.8 mmHg·s/mL
   (aortic pressure tracks LV ejection more closely)

4. ESPVR drawing: back-calculated through actual simulation-derived end-systolic
   point (V0_eff = ESV - ESP/Ees) rather than trusting the V0 slider directly

5. PVA potential energy geometry: corrected from triangular approximation to
   proper integration bounded by ESPVR (top), IVR vertical at ESV (right),
   and EDPVR curve (bottom)

6. Extended with: valvular pathologies (AS, AR, MS, MR), Stage 5 interventions
   (pre/post TAVR, MVR, CRT-P), 6 UI themes (CSS variables), mobile Canvas2D
   renderer, EDPVR Scale and Slope independent sliders, teaching notes and
   educational stage banners throughout

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EDUCATIONAL USE DISCLAIMER
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

CardioMechanics is intended for educational purposes only. It must not be used
for clinical decision-making, patient management, or diagnosis. All physiological
values are simplified model approximations. The simulator does not replace
clinical judgment, medical training, or professional advice.
